title: For Sale:   P38 Walther AC-45 1st Variation Matching Excellent
postcontent: This WW2 production Walther manufactured AC-45 P38 based on the ‘c’ letter serial number range, fit, finish, E/359 inspection markings and other features - is a late war 1st variation model produced in early 1945. Per ’Axis Pistols’ Volume 2 (J. Still), serials of the 1st variation approximately range from 1-2000c. Chambered for 9mm this pistol appears to be 100% period correct, non-import marked, with all matching numbers on the frame, slide, barrel and locking block. The original mixed blue and phosphate finished components appear correct, in overall excellent condition but do show some minor wear, spotting, and fading. Mechanics appear to be excellent. The matching number barrel is excellent and bright with strong lands and grooves. The original black grips appear to be un-chipped or cracked and show wear consistent with the rest of the assembly. The excellent condition magazine appears to function properly and shows wear consistent with the rest of the assembly. Magazine is a properly finished, later war variation for Walther, marked ‘P. 38v’ and Walther inspected E/359. Overall this is an excellent example of a very desirable, late war, combat pistol, which had time to see the final days of brutal combat in WW2.Money order, money gram , walmart to walmart will ship faster, we do not accept check.
